cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and specifically on human detection, which falls under the sub-category of object detection. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel approach using deep learning techniques, which involves training a neural network to detect humans in crowded scenarios. This makes it likely that the paper could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of efficient algorithms for feature aggregation and post-processing, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
